#Text=Wikinews interviews UK pro darts player Kirk Shepherd
#Text=Thursday , October 30 , 2008
#Text=Kirk
#Text=Shepherd
#Text=is a professional darts player from the United Kingdom .
#Text=Kirk began playing competitively at 13 for his local pub , and was soon crowned Boys Champion at the Winmau World Masters in 2003 .
#Text=Shepherd was voted Young Player of the Year by the British Darts Organisation in 2005 and 2006 .
#Text=Shepherd is perhaps best known for his performance at the 2008 PDC World Darts Championship .

#Text=Forced to qualify for the televised tournament , he then proceeded to knock out a number of well-known players live on television , including Terry Jenkins , Wayne Mardle and former finalist Peter Manley .
#Text=He ultimately went on to come second in the tournament , becoming the youngest ever finalist , and losing out to John Part in the final .
#Text=He has also previously managed to defeat the then world number one , Gary Anderson .
#Text=Due to his performance at the world championship he will play in this year 's Grand Slam of Darts next month .
#Text=Ahead of that appearance Wikinews was able to conduct an interview with Kirk , which is now available below :
#Text=Interview
#Text=Wikinews
#Text=The Grand Slam 's coming up soon .
#Text=Do you feel confident you can do well in another major tournament ?
#Text=Yes , I believe in my own ability and know I 've got the game to beat anyone on my day .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) How 's this year been going so far ?
#Text=Not as well as I would have hoped , but I wont let that rock my confidence .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) When you were at the world championships , did you find playing top-level darts players daunting ?
#Text=No , I was more exited about it more than anything .
#Text=I had previously played top players before and won so I knew I could cut it out with the best .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) How do you approach a match as an underdog without giving up immediately ?
#Text=I just believe in my self and confidence is a key factor .

#Text=( ( WN ) ) Your website says that in playing darts live on TV and defeating the world number one at the time — Gary Anderson — you have achieved two of your aims . What are your other aims , and when do you hope to achieve them ?
#Text=My aims are to break in the top 16 which I hope to do by next year and to be a world champion ; my aim for this is in the next 5 years .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Who are your darting heroes ?
#Text=Dennis Priestley
#Text=( ( WN ) ) What first got you interested in darts ?
#Text=My dad was a keen player so I followed in his footsteps , I guess .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) What were your your ambitions before you entered darts professionally , or was that what you had always wanted to do ?
#Text=Darts has always been my life , I always wanted to be a pro darts player .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Do you see yourself joining the premier league in a few years ?
#Text=That would be a great achievement .
#Text=If I could make this another good run in this years world championship [ that ] would see me there .
#Text=I think i can do it .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) What do you think you would be doing now if it was n't for darts ?
#Text=I would probably go in to the plumbing trade .
